      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Good things — even some great things — are happening! It’s been a historic week for the labor movement. Workers at a Staten Island Amazon warehouse have overcome the odds and voted to form the first-ever U.S. labor union at one of the world’s most powerful companies. "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "The Lever"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "'s reporter Matthew Cunningham-Cook, who spent six years working as a strategic researcher and educator for unions, breaks down what the victory means."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Meanwhile, federal regulators have moved to block TurboTax from misleading Americans this tax season. And protestors will descend upon Washington D.C. next week to demand that President Joe Biden make good on his promise to cancel student debt."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "All this and much more in this week’s edition of You Love To See It."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "h3",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "AMAZON WORKERS PULL OFF HISTORIC VICTORY"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "The victory for the Amazon Labor Union at the 8,000-worker Staten Island warehouse is easily the biggest victory for the labor movement since the successful "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            1
          ],
          1,
          "1997"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " UPS strike. The tiny independent union that had no dues payers and was "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            2
          ],
          1,
          "headed"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " by Christian Smalls, the Amazon worker fired for protesting the company’s lack of COVID-19 protocols in March 2020, is one for the history books. You cannot find a bigger David versus Goliath labor victory — with no resources on the union side, versus the country’s second largest employer — since at least the 1940s. The final vote count was "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            3
          ],
          1,
          "2654-2131"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ", an incredible 11 percent margin of victory."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "“The Amazon Labor Union is feeling the power of the people and the vote demonstrates our labor power and the hard work we’ve put into this campaign,” worker Brett Daniels "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            4
          ],
          1,
          "told"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " Luis Feliz Leon at Labor Notes."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      10,
      3
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "In addition to my work as a union staffer, I’ve been writing about labor for over a decade. I never saw this coming. Amazon was too powerful an employer, labor law so "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            5
          ],
          1,
          "tilted"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " to the bosses, and the ALU had no resources whatsoever. I kept my mouth shut because I never want to hurt others’ efforts to organize, but I was very skeptical. No more. The ALU victory mandates a total recalibration of labor’s approach to organizing the unorganized."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "As "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "Labor Notes"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " staff writer Jonah Furman "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            6
          ],
          1,
          "noted"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ", “No corporate campaign, very little $$$, picked a workplace and targeted the shit out of it. Was very much not stage-managed. Why did this work? The big unions need to answer those questions.”"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "As I was texting with other folks in labor who have collectively organized thousands of workers yesterday, we were all in shock. Is the win actually possible? Turns out it was. All credit to Smalls and his ragtag group of organizers working long hours for next to no pay, who beat Jeff Bezos’ $1.6 trillion behemoth. Amazon "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            7
          ],
          1,
          "retained"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " a top Democratic polling firm, Global Strategy Group, for this fight, and last year, the retail giant put at least "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            8
          ],
          1,
          "$4.3 million"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " into union busting activities (a number which does "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            9
          ],
          1,
          "not include"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " a much broader array of undisclosed union busting services provided by major law firms, such as "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            10
          ],
          1,
          "Morgan Lewis"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ")."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "The workers have got a long road ahead of them to get a contract. While there isn’t much recent research on the topic, roughly one quarter of union victories "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            11
          ],
          1,
          "do not result"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " in a first contract. This is likely higher at large companies like Amazon that do not have any union density. (Bezos’ "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "Washington Post"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " is union, however, and Amazon Studios hires union labor in Hollywood.) This will assuredly be Amazon’s game plan: to delay, obstruct, and depress workers after they have won this incredible victory."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "But ALU does have one very smart strategic trick up its sleeve: It’s moving to organize more workers. They’ve already filed for election at a smaller Amazon warehouse on Staten Island, this time with 1,500 workers. That election will "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            12
          ],
          1,
          "begin"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " on April 25. A "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            13
          ],
          1,
          "victory"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " for the separate Retail, Wholesale, and Department Store Union at Amazon’s warehouse in Bessemer, Alabama, would also provide a shot in the arm to ALU’s efforts to get a contract — though it could take months, if not more, to suss out the voting results there, due to the right-wing judiciary."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "It’s in this fight for a first contract where support from elected officials will be desperately needed. While Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez (D-N.Y.) "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            14
          ],
          1,
          "caught"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " some flack yesterday from Smalls for not showing up during the organizing campaign, she could rebuild those bridges by working closely with ALU as they head into this knock-down, drag-out fight for a contract. In particular, tighter scrutiny of Amazon’s "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            15
